<%@ Page Language="C#" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="Instructions.aspx.cs" Inherits="SMIU_Admission.Instructions"
    MasterPageFile="~/MasterPages/student.Master" EnableEventValidation="false" %>

<asp:Content ID="Content1" runat="server" ContentPlaceHolderID="cphbody">
    <p>
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> Read all the following instructions carefully before attempting
        the test</p>
    <br />
    <p>
        <strong>INSTRUCTIONS: </strong>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>At the following screen, log in with your email and password, provided at the time
            of admission application submission. </li>
        <li>Entry test consists of <strong>60 Questions</strong>, with <strong>15 Questions
        </strong>in each of the 4 sections. </li>
        <li>Total test duration is <strong>60 Minutes</strong>. If you fail to submit the test
            within allocated time limit then test will be submitted automatically. </li>
        <li>Each question carries equal marks </li>
        <li>There is no negative marking in the Entry Test.</li>
        <li>For rough work, a separate sheet has been provided. Kindly use wisely as no extra
            sheet will be provided</li>
        <li>Use of mobile phone, calculator or any sort of electronic device(s) is strictly
            prohibited.</li>
        <li>Any attempt of malpractices, discussion or borrowing stationery from others will
            be considered as disqualification from entrance test.</li>
        <li>No extra time will be provided to latecomers.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        <strong>DIRECTIONS FOR ATTEMPTING TEST</strong></p>
    <ol>
        <li>At a time, one question will appear on the candidate&rsquo;s screen. You can either
            select the most suitable answer or select <strong>&ldquo;NEXT&rdquo;</strong> to
            skip question. If you are unsure of the answer, you can always come back to the
            question.</li>
        <li>Mark circle/box with the most suitable option</li>
        <li>You cannot select more than 1 options</li>
        <li>Use <strong>&ldquo;PREVIOUS&rdquo;</strong> and <strong>&ldquo;NEXT&rdquo;</strong>
            buttons to navigate among the questions.</li>
    </ol>
    <br />
    <a href="/index.aspx" style="background-color:forestgreen; color:white; border:1px solid green; padding:10px; border-radius:5px; padding-left:30px; padding-right:30px;">Proceed</a>
    <br />
    <br />
</asp:Content>
